{"tid":2179064,"cid":33,"subCid":0,"title":"【隱性侵粉】11.7%共和黨選民不向民調機構表示意向","createTime":"2020-08-29T00:16:15.000Z","updateTime":"2020-08-29T08:37:53.000Z","uid":289191,"like":11,"dislike":0,"uniUserReply":7,"replies":[{"pid":"32ba763bed84cbb3d6d4e1496213e85542288c8e","tid":2179064,"uid":289191,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-29T00:16:15.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.zerohedge.com/political/silent-majority-over-10-trump-voters-wont-admit-preferences-pollsters\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zerohedge.com%2Fpolitical%2Fsilent-majority-over-10-trump-voters-wont-admit-preferences-pollsters&d=aJB%2Bq6ruafnyRbkwc%2FW5ZotKjO%2FIGoH7AJS0Ocrd4mI%3D&h=bcedd0f4\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.zerohedge.com/political/silent-majority-over-10-trump-voters-wont-admit-preferences-pollsters</a><br />\nA new study from CloudResearch reveals that 11.7% of Republicans won't admit their political preferences to pollsters - which is more than twice the number of Democrats at just 5.4%.<br />\n民主黨只有5.4%會隱藏意向。"},{"pid":"ad88c07bf05c7a22ed592872ff78c0e072d505bf","tid":2179064,"uid":289191,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-29T00:17:15.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/wmSizOF.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FwmSizOF.jpg&h=fc0d25d1&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"0d3f700c96eb53982c031b1b3d25de68a262afbb","tid":2179064,"uid":289191,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-29T00:19:09.000Z","msg":"CloudResearch also found that &quot;10.5% of Independents fell into the &quot;shy voter&quot; category, just a percentage point lower than how Republicans react to phone polls.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nWhen asked why they wouldn't be truthful in their responses, &quot;shy&quot; respondents cited six concerns:"},{"pid":"45925a57f4b1d018fdece940947884910d2440d0","tid":2179064,"uid":289191,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-29T00:20:35.000Z","msg":"1. A lack of trust in phone polls as truly being anonymous. <br />\n<br />\n2. An apprehension to associate their phone numbers with recorded responses.<br />\n<br />\n3. Fear that their responses will become public in some manner.<br />\n<br />\n4. Fear of reprisal and related detrimental impact to their financial, social, and family lives should their political opinions become publicly known. <br />\n<br />\n5. A general dislike of phone polls. <br />\n<br />\n6. Malicious intent to mislead polls due to general distrust of media and political pundits (though a sentiment expressed only by a few &ldquo;shy voters&rdquo;)."},{"pid":"ea0b391a2e4f971cd1dcc8a2b4e73bec4dd9dabc","tid":2179064,"uid":127575,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-29T02:29:48.000Z","msg":"沉默大多數<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/hoho.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"f7c5d5f5f997766aea3d48e6f0cbe96fb3e1b5b0","tid":2179064,"uid":357030,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-29T03:06:15.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/clap.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/clap.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/clap.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5d30026df0eaad8ce7bba9652043644adf6b6282","tid":2179064,"uid":127575,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-08-29T03:36:05.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/hoho.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"22b29331630606a6cf3b702c1974c6b33a66fae3","tid":2179064,"uid":371606,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-08-29T03:41:09.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/support.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/support.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\nTrump 粉"},{"pid":"9e11edbc3a985454ead17938dc0463185e310574","tid":2179064,"uid":127575,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"22b29331630606a6cf3b702c1974c6b33a66fae3","tid":2179064,"uid":371606,"like":1